comment.author: 67349057@N06
comment._content: This was probably 1932 when Winterhude arrived in Sydney 83 days out of Callao, Peru. She had lost her fore royal mast in 1923 reducing the sails on her foremast to 5. In 1934 she lost her main royal mast in a collision with a bridge. Neither was replaced.  Robert Carter
